    <!-- 1. What is R -->
    <view class="card">
      <text class="cardTitle">What is R?</text>
      <text class="desc" lang="en">R is a powerful and open-source programming language and software environment specifically designed for statistical computing, data analysis, and graphical visualization. Widely used by statisticians, data scientists, and researchers, it offers a vast repository of packages (such as those in CRAN) that extend its functionality for specialized tasks like machine learning, bioinformatics, and financial modeling.</text>
    </view>

    <!-- 2. The Advantages of R -->
    <view class="card">
      <text class="cardTitle">The Advantages of R</text>
      <view class="list">
        <view class="listItem">• Powerful statistical modeling and analysis packages (regression, time series, factor analysis, testing).</view>
        <view class="listItem">• High-quality visualization: ggplot2, plotly, echarts4r, suitable for publication-ready charts.</view>
        <view class="listItem">• Rapid prototyping and report automation: R Markdown / Quarto / Shiny.</view>
        <view class="listItem">• Rich ecosystem of academic and industry packages (biostatistics, econometrics, financial risk management, etc.).</view>
      </view>
    </view>

    <!-- 3. Typical Roles and Scenarios in Enterprises -->
    <view class="card">
      <text class="cardTitle">Typical Roles and Scenarios in Enterprises</text>
      <view class="list">
        <view class="listItem">• Internal analysts / data scientists: Metric definition, A/B testing analysis, model building.</view>
        <view class="listItem">• Business Intelligence (BI) and reporting: Automated weekly/monthly reports, KPI dashboards (for internal use).</view>
        <view class="listItem">• Risk management/Finance/Pharmaceutical industries: Statistical testing, clinical trial analysis, risk models.</view>
        <view class="listItem">• R output → Front-end/Product: Providing data via JSON/CSV or APIs (Plumber).</view>
        <view class="listItem">• Of Course, R is also extensively used in Academia.</view>
      </view>
    </view>

    <!-- 4. What Can R bring to Your Career? -->
    <view class="card">
      <text class="cardTitle">What Can R Bring to Your Career?</text>
      <text class="desc">Data analysis & amp; R skills are highly demanded in medicine, finance, internet industry. Job openings include data analyst, visualization engineer, BI developer etc.</text>
    </view>

